---
---

<section class="relative py-12 md:py-16">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6">
    <div class="reveal mb-4 text-center">
      <p class="mb-3 text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[#818cf8]">Measured, Not Claimed</p>
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-4xl" style="font-family: var(--font-display)">Benchmarks</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-base text-[#94a3b8]">
        We built the same Task Management API in Kōdo, Python, TypeScript, Rust, and Go.
        Then we measured what matters for AI agents. All code is
        <a href="https://github.com/rfunix/kodo/tree/main/benchmarks" class="text-[#818cf8] hover:text-[#a5b4fc] transition">open source</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal-stagger mt-10 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">

      <!-- Compile-Time Safety -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.06] bg-[#0f1019]/50 p-7 text-center">
        <div class="mb-4 inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-indigo-500/10">
          <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-[#818cf8]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" /></svg>
        </div>
        <p class="mb-1 text-4xl font-bold text-[#f8fafc]" style="font-family: var(--font-display)">7/7</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-[#818cf8]">Compile-Time Bug Classes</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[13px] text-[#94a3b8]/70">Contracts and refinement types catch nulls, type errors, range violations, invalid state transitions, and more — before the code runs.</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[12px] text-[#94a3b8]/50">Rust: 4/7 &middot; TypeScript: 2/7 &middot; Go: 2/7 &middot; Python: 0/7</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Error Readability -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.06] bg-[#0f1019]/50 p-7 text-center">
        <div class="mb-4 inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-indigo-500/10">
          <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-[#818cf8]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 20l4-16m4 4l4 4-4 4M6 16l-4-4 4-4" /></svg>
        </div>
        <p class="mb-1 text-4xl font-bold text-[#f8fafc]" style="font-family: var(--font-display)">5/5</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-[#818cf8]">Error Machine-Readability</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[13px] text-[#94a3b8]/70">Structured JSON errors with byte-offset fix patches. Agents parse errors and apply fixes without guessing.</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[12px] text-[#94a3b8]/50">Rust: 3/5 &middot; TypeScript: 2/5 &middot; Go: 1/5 &middot; Python: 1/5</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Agent Features -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.06] bg-[#0f1019]/50 p-7 text-center">
        <div class="mb-4 inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-indigo-500/10">
          <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-[#818cf8]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" /></svg>
        </div>
        <p class="mb-1 text-4xl font-bold text-[#f8fafc]" style="font-family: var(--font-display)">9</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-[#818cf8]">Agent-Specific Features</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[13px] text-[#94a3b8]/70">Contracts, traceability, confidence scores, intents, certificates, MCP — built into the language, not bolted on.</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-[12px] text-[#94a3b8]/50">Features that don't exist in general-purpose languages</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Honest context -->
    <div class="reveal mt-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.04] bg-[#0f1019]/30 px-7 py-5">
      <p class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-[#94a3b8]/70">
        <span class="font-medium text-[#94a3b8]">A note on fairness:</span>
        This benchmark measures compile-time safety and agent-specific features — areas where Kōdo was explicitly designed to excel.
        It does not measure runtime performance, ecosystem maturity, or general-purpose productivity, where established languages have years of advantage.
        Python uses fewer tokens for the same functionality. Rust has a more mature ownership system.
        We present these numbers transparently and explain exactly how each score was calculated.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal mt-6 text-center">
      <a href="/docs/reference/benchmarks/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-[#818cf8]/20 bg-[#818cf8]/5 px-5 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-[#818cf8] transition hover:bg-[#818cf8]/10">
        Full methodology and results
        <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" /></svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
